<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="433" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,372,864]" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1324654195" collectionCode="DNA" location="However" municipality="Pleistocene" pageId="32" pageNumber="433" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Eastern">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,732,757]" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,562,732,756]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="32" pageNumber="433" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ctenactis">
<emphasis box="[323,562,732,756]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">Pyrgopolon ctenactis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from a few localities in the Tropical 
<collectingRegion box="[1121,1205,733,756]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Eastern" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">Eastern</collectingRegion>
Pacific. The Pacific population of this subtidal species might be a 
<collectingMunicipality box="[666,794,767,792]" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">Pleistocene</collectingMunicipality>
relict, the taxon was never reported from ship hulls, thus dispersion as fouling of ships is unlikely. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:EC3987858730FFE0FF24F8B85873FCEA:614F6048870FFFE0FD3AFC9C59B0FCB6" box="[649,753,805,828]" municipality="Pleistocene" name="However" pageId="32" pageNumber="433" stateProvince="Eastern">However</location>
, a thorough review and comparison 
<locationDeviation pageId="32" pageNumber="433">between Atlantic and Pacific</locationDeviation>
populations is necessary, including a 
<collectionCode box="[652,713,840,864]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">DNA</collectionCode>
analysis.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
